e=}}</ref> [[Oakey Army Aviation Centre]] (training base)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mindef.gov.sg/web/portal/mindef/error/error404 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2018-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180914203232/https://www.mindef.gov.sg/web/portal/mindef/error/error404 |archive-date=2018-09-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* {{flagu|New Zealand}} \u2013 [[RNZAF Base Ohakea]] (training base)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/manawatu-standard/news/94864316/singapore-air-force-flies-in-to-ohakea-for-flying-training|title=Singapore Air Force flies in to Ohakea for flying training|website=stuff|date=2 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=11807172|title=NZ could host Singapore's fighter jets at Ohakea|website=nzherald|date=25 February 2017}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|United States}} \u2013 [[Mountain Home Air Force Base]] (training base);<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mountainhome.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/309801/republic-of-singapore-air-force-begins-arriving-at-mountain-home-afb/|title=Republic of Singapore air force begins arriving at Mountain Home AFB|website=mountainhome.af.mil|date=1 October 2008}}</ref> [[Luke Air Force Base]] (training base)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.luke.af.mil/News/Commentaries/Display/Article/641514/us-singapore-partnership-standout/|title=U.S., Singapore partnership standout|website=luke.af.mil|date=22 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Turkey== \n* {{flagu|Azerbaijan}} \u2013 Buildings and structures in Gizil Sherg military town, and one terminal building located in the airfield in [[Hac\u0131 Zeynalabdin]] settlement.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkey-to-establish-military-base-in-azerbaijan.aspx?pageID=238&nID=101906&NewsCatID=353|title=Turkey to establish military base in Azerbaijan \u2013 EURASIA|website=H\u00fcrriyet Daily News \u2013 LEADING NEWS SOURCE FOR TURKEY AND THE REGION}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Northern Cyprus}} (