 Hosts Attack Aircraft and Chinese Drones |first=Tyler |last=Rogoway |date=October 27, 2016 |publisher=The Drive Media, Inc |quote=Some of these nations even have their own forward operating bases in Libya, including a secretive remote airfield operated by the United Arab Emirates and located about 50 miles southeast of Benghazi. Here, the UAE has deployed a pocket air force of heavily armed and armored agricultural planes developed into surveillance and light attack platforms\u2013the AT-802U Border Patrol variant of the Air Tractor and the more capable IOMAX Archangel\u2013in addition to S-70 Blackhawks, and Chinese Wing Loong unmanned aircraft}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.libyaherald.com/2016/10/28/uae-operating-an-airbase-near-marj-report/ |newspaper=[[Libya Herald]] |title=UAE operating an airbase near Marj: report |date=October 26, 2016 |quote=IHS Jane\u2019s says that the UAE is operating propeller-driven AT-802U light aircraft, helicopters and surveillance drones from the Al-Khadim airport to the south-east of Marj and Jardas Al-Abid.}}</ref>\n*{{flagu|Somaliland}} ([[Somalia]])\u2013 Military base in the [[Port of Berbera]].<ref name=\"uae-berbera\">{{cite web|title=Somaliland agrees to UAE military base in Berbera|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-38956093|date=13 February 2017|accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Yemen}} \u2013 Partial military base in the island of [[Socotra]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Anger erupts on Yemen's Socotra as UAE deploys over 100 troops|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/05/anger-erupts-yemen-socotra-uae-deploys-100-troops-180503072636773.html|accessdate=3 May 2018|work=Al-Jazeera}}</ref><ref name=MEM>{{cite news|title=UAE forces beef-up presence in Yemen\u2019s Socotra Island|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20180503-uae-forces-beef-up-presence-in-yemens-socotra-island/|accessdate=3 May 2018|work=Middle East Monitor|date=3 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==United Kingdom==\n{{Main|Overseas military bases of the United Kingdom}}\n[[File:United Kingdom military bases worldwide.png|thumb|upright=2|Some major military bases and facilities of the United Kingdom.]]\n\n*{{flagu|Afghanistan}} \u2013 Various facilities under [[Operation Toral]]\n*{{flagu|Bahrain}} \u2013 [[HMS Jufair|HMS Jufair Naval Base]] (HMNBJ)<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/construction-begins-on-new-base-for-the-royal-navy-in-bahrain Construction begins on new base for the Royal Navy in Bahrain], www.gov.uk, 31 October 2015</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Royal Navy's new Bahrain base seriously enhances Britain's ability to defend the Gulf|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/10/todays-opening-of-the-royal-navys-new-bahrain-base-seriously-enh/|accessdate=17 November 2016|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=10 November 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Belize}} \u2013 [[British Army Training and Support Unit Belize]]<ref name=\"SDSR2015\">{{cite web|title=National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/478933/52309_Cm_9161_NSS_SD_Review_web_only.pdf|date=November 2015|publisher=HM Government|accessdate=23 November 2015}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Brunei}} \u2013 [[British Forces Brunei]]: Brunei Garrison<ref name=\"Brunei\">{{cite web|title=The British Army in Brunei|url=http://www.army.mod.uk/operations-deployments/22792.aspx|website=www.army.mod.uk/|publisher=Ministry of Defence|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Canada}} \u2013 [[British Army Training Unit Suffield]]<ref name=\"Canada British Army Training Unit\">{{cite web|title=The British Army in Canada|url=http://www.army.mod.uk/operations-deployments/22727.aspx|website=www.army.mod.uk/|publisher=Ministry of Defence|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Republic of Cyprus}} \u2013 [[RAF Troodos]]\n* {{flagu|Estonia}} \u2013 UK led Battlegroup in Tapa: [[NATO Enhanced Forward Presence]]<ref name=\"UK led Enhanced Forward Presence\">{{cite web