is and cyber warfare|url=https://www.ft.com/content/4d16d268-629b-11e4-9838-00144feabdc0|newspaper=Financial Times|date=3 November 2014|accessdate=23 March 2017|url-access=subscription }}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Oman}} \u2013 Omani-British Joint Training Base;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/uk-cements-position-in-gulf-with-new-joint-base-in-oman|title=UK cements position in Gulf with new joint base in Oman|date=5 November 2018|accessdate=24 April 2019|publisher=gov.uk}}</ref> Duqm<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/defence-secretary-strengthens-ties-between-uk-and-oman|title=Defence Secretary strengthens ties between UK and Oman|date=28 August 2017|accessdate=24 April 2019|publisher=gov.uk}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|United Arab Emirates}} \u2013 [[Al Minhad Air Base]]\n* {{flagu|United States}} \u2013 [[Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort|MCAS Beaufort]] (training base),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/defence-minister-reaffirms-us-uk-collaboration-on-major-equipment-programmes|title=Defence Minister Reaffirms US UK Collaboration On Major Equipment Programs|website=www.gov.uk|}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f35.com/about/who-is-flying/locations-mcas-beaufort|title=Who Is Flying Locations MCAS Beaufort|website=www.f35.com|}}</ref> [[Creech Air Force Base]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.defenceprocurementinternational.com/features/air/the-royal-air-forces-reaper-squadron|title=Eyes In The Sky, But At What Cost?|website=www.defenceprocurementinternational.com|access-date=2019-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nellis.af.mil/News/Article/285884/royal-air-force-activates-uav-squadron-at-creech-afb/|title=Royal Air Force Activates UAV Squadron at Creech AFB|website=Nellis Air Force Base|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-20}}</ref> [[Edwards Air Force Base]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/uk-f-35-lightning-ii-testing-begins-in-the-us|title=UK F-35 Lightning II testing begins in the 