aval Base]]\n* {{flagu|Netherlands}} \u2013 [[Volkel Air Base]]; [[USCG Activities Europe]]\n* {{flagu|Niger}} \u2013 [[Niger Air Base 201]]\n* {{flagu|Norway}} \u2013 Marine Corps garrison at [[V\u00e6rnes Air Station]]\n* {{flagu|Oman}} \u2013 [[RAFO Masirah]]; RAFO [[Thumrait]] (South of Oman) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/facility/thumrait.htm|title=Thumrait Air Base|last=Pike|first=John|website=www.globalsecurity.org|access-date=2017-02-02}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Philippines}} \u2013 [[Antonio Bautista Air Base]]; [[Basa Air Base]]; [[Fort Magsaysay]]; [[Lumbia Air Base]]; [[Mactan-Benito Ebuen Air Base]]<ref>[http://www.officialgazette.gov.ph/2014/04/29/document-enhanced-defense-cooperation-agreement/ Enhanced Defense Cooperation Agreement (EDCA)], officialgazette.gov.ph</ref>\n* {{flagu|Portugal}} \u2013 [[Lajes Field]]\n* {{flagu|Qatar}} \u2013 [[Al Udeid Air Base]]\n* {{flagu|Romania}} \u2013 [[Mihail Kog\u0103lniceanu International Airport]]; [[Deveselu]]\n* {{flagu|Saudi Arabia}} \u2013 [[64th Air Expeditionary Group]] (inactive since 2014);<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afcent.af.mil/Units/379th-Air-Expeditionary-Wing/News/Display/Article/501563/64th-air-expeditionary-group-deactivated/|title=64th Air Expeditionary Group Deactivated|work=U.S. Air Forces Central Command|access-date=2018-09-08|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Prince Sultan Air Base]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/pentagon-to-deploy-around-2-000-additional-troops-to-saudi-arabia-11570809038?mod=article_inline|title=Pentagon to Deploy Around 2,000 Additional Troops to Saudi Arabia|website=The Wall Street Journal|date=11 October 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Singapore}} \u2013 [[Paya Lebar Air Base]]\n* {{flagu|South Korea}} \u2013 [[United States Forces Korea]]\n* {{flagu|Spain}} \u2013 [[Mor\u00f3n Air Base]]; [[Naval Station Rota]]\n* {{flagu|Syria}} \u2013 Military base in [[Al-Tanf (U.S. military base)|Al-Tanf]] and several facilities in northern Syria, withi